nba.stats: The Los Angeles Lakers are an American professional basketball team based in Los Angeles. The Lakers compete in the National Basketball Association, as a member of the league's Western Conference in the Pacific Division. The Los Angeles Lakers have the second-highest all-time NBA regular season win-loss record percentage (.594) among all current NBA teams.

The Boston Celtics are an American professional basketball team based in Boston, Massachusetts. The Boston Celtics have the third-highest all-time NBA regular season win-loss record percentage (.590) among all current NBA teams.

The Philadelphia 76ers are an American professional basketball team based in the Philadelphia metropolitan area. They have won three NBA championships, with their first coming as the Syracuse Nationals in 1955. The second title came in 1967, a team which was led by Chamberlain. The third title came in 1983, won by a team led by Erving and Malone.
